The paper is about a convolutional neural network architecture for fine-grained visual recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses transfer learning, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves collaboration between features learned from training samples, which is a form of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions experiments and results, which are often associated with neural networks and optimization (cs.NE). Lastly, the paper introduces a new dataset, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM).
